Subaru Southern Africa has appointed Andrew Marshall as its new MD from June 1. Marshall has more than 20 years' experience in the automotive sector. His management experience includes four years as regional manager for CFAO Malawi, three years as Toyota Malawi GM, four years as Toyota Zambia MD and eight years as Toyota Tsusho Africa GM. Marshall also established the Japanese Subaru brand in Zambia during his tenure as MD. “I look forward to steering Subaru through these unprecedented and uncertain times,” says Marshall. “We have an enthusiastic and thriving dealer network that is wanting of a broader customer base. “With this renewed energy, our shareholders and manufacturer are steadfast in further investing in our market. “This all bodes well for our mandate of delivering superior confidence in all that we do for our customers.” Marshall succeeds outgoing MD Rui Silva, who has opted to pursue other opportunities.